  "prompt": "What was Jesus like as a child?",
  "response": "The childhood of Jesus is not extensively documented in the Bible, but there are a few key points that provide some insight. According to the Gospel of Luke, Jesus was born in Bethlehem and later moved to Nazareth with his family. One of the most notable events from his childhood is found in Luke 2:41-52, which describes Jesus at the age of twelve visiting the temple in Jerusalem. During this visit, Jesus engages with the teachers in the temple, astonishing them with his understanding and answers.\n\nFrom the limited biblical accounts, it can be inferred that Jesus was an exceptionally wise and spiritually perceptive child. He demonstrated a profound understanding of religious teachings and a strong sense of his divine mission even at a young age. Beyond the biblical narratives, there are varying accounts and traditions in other texts, but they are not considered canonical by mainstream Christianity.\n\nThe Bible also emphasizes that Jesus grew up in a humble, devout Jewish family, adhering to religious customs and engaging in everyday life. He likely experienced the typical upbringing of a Jewish boy in Nazareth, learning carpentry from his father, Joseph, and participating in community life.\n\nOverall, while there are only a few stories about Jesus' childhood in the Bible, they highlight his early wisdom, deep spiritual insight, and normal upbringing in a devout Jewish family.",
